      "rationale": "In-vitro experiments used porcine blood with hematocrit controlled to 33 ± 2%. Temperature was maintained at 37 ± 1°C. However, pump inlet pressure was not independently measured during hemolysis trials, and uncertainty in blood viscosity due to donor variability was not formally propagated into the experimental reference values."
    },
    {
