      "acceptanceCriteria": "Formal justification for the choice of hemolysis damage model (power-law Giersiepen-Wurzinger or equivalent) and turbulence closure, including sensitivity analysis of model form uncertainty on hemolysis predictions.",
      "rationale": "The Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law hemolysis model was selected based on literature precedent. No formal model form uncertainty analysis or comparison of alternative hemolysis models was conducted. This is the most significant epistemic gap identified at MRL 5."
